  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lok II Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lok II (Lok II or the Company) is a limited liability company to be established under the laws of Mauritius, with a term of 10 years, dedicated to investing and supporting the microfinance sector in India.  The Company intends to raise $80 Million in total commitments and seeks to make 10-12 equity or quasi-equity or equity-linked investments in microfinance institutions and companies that support the growth and sustainability of the microfinance ecosystem including micro-insurance, housing finance, mobile payments, remittances, healthcare and education.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment is expected to have the following development impact: i) increase access to finance by reaching low-income families through MFIs, ii) provide goods and services to low-income families by investing in companies that serve the BoP, iii) build institutional capacity through technical assistance, and iv) support the growth of the microfinance sector.</narrative>
  </description>
